# Infrastructure documentation and scripting

## Document every action

When creating, changing, or running infrastructure (Cloudflare Workers, D1, R2,
Queues, DNS, Access, secrets workflow, deploy/provision CI), update the matching
docs in the same change:

| Change area | Primary docs |
|---|---|
| Bootstrap / resources / Access / zone | `docs/provision.md` |
| Deploy tiers, CI, promote path | `docs/deployment.md` |
| Live resource IDs / names | `docs/inventory-dev.md`, `docs/inventory-production.md` |

Also keep package scripts and `wrangler.jsonc` bindings consistent with those
docs.

## What to write (and not write)

- Document **what** a script or step does and **why** it exists.
- Do **not** narrate script internals, control flow, or line-by-line logic.
- Prefer tables, checklists, and `npm run …` entry points over prose dumps.
- After any infra change, refresh stale claims (status, hostnames, IDs, “manual
  vs scripted”).

## Prefer scripts over ad-hoc commands

- One-time / bootstrap infrastructure lives under `infra-setup/` (e.g.
  `provision-*.sh`, hostname attach) and is invoked via npm scripts — not
  one-off shell history. Ongoing runtime helpers (seed, smoke, parity) stay
  under `scripts/`.
- Genuinely simpler one-offs (login, single `secret put`, dashboard enablement)
  are allowed **only if** they are recorded in `docs/provision.md` (or the
  table above) as manual/semi-scripted steps.
- Never leave a new resource, binding, hostname, or Access app undocumented.

## Local Cloudflare API tokens (`.env.cloudflare`)

- User stores tokens in **gitignored** `.env.cloudflare` (template:
  `.env.cloudflare.example`). Scripts under `infra-setup/` load it via
  `infra-setup/lib/common.sh` (`load_cloudflare_env` / `require_api_token`).
- Agents **must** invoke those npm/scripts so the shell sources the file.
  Agents must **not** `Read`, `cat`, or otherwise open `.env.cloudflare` to
  extract or display token values. Prefer telling the user to fill the file
  locally over asking them to paste a token into chat.

## Examples

```text
✅ Add infra-setup/provision-foo.sh + npm run provision:foo, then document
   purpose and when to run it in docs/provision.md; refresh inventory if IDs change.

❌ Run wrangler/API one-liners to create prod resources and commit wrangler.jsonc
   with no doc/inventory update.

❌ Paste the full bash script into docs/ — link the npm script and state outcomes.
```
